In this paper, we model an automated negotiation problem as a Partially Observable Markov Decision Process with a specific focus on personality types. We focus on four personality types, in particular, namely Individualist, Cooperator, Competitor, and Altruist. We generated 30 negotiation transcripts for each type for experimentation purposes using the IAGO software. For purposes of sanity check: (a) We compared our POMDP against two MDPs, MDP1, which does not model personality type and MDP2, which knows the personality type. We found MDP1 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
